Limpopo police are searching for a group of criminals responsible for the murder of a man whose charred body was discovered outside Lebowakgamo. JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo police are searching for a group of criminals responsible for the murder of a man whose charred body was discovered outside Lebowakgamo. A passerby made the grim discovery on Friday after stumbling on what remained of a torched car. Police have not yet established the age, race or gender of the victim. Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said, “Police have launched a manhunt for the suspects involved in the killing of an unknown person. the motive is still unknown.”